ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Did you ever lose a lot of weight on purpose, or while you were growing up, did you keep your weight down on purpose?

If DK, did friends say you were too thin or skeleton-like?
How tall were you at that time (feet)?
How tall were you at that time (inches)?
How old were you?
At the time, were you intensely afraid of gaining weight or becoming fat?
At that time (when you lost the most weight on purpose), did you, yourself, think that you were so thin that your health was in danger?
While you were losing weight did your period stop for 3 or more cycles in a row (when you were not pregnant or taking hormones, like estrogen)?
Notes: 1 = No; 5 = Yes; 999 = Missing. If R is male, skip to ED8

ElementDescription: Was there a medical disorder that caused your weight loss?
Notes: 1 = No; 5 = Yes (Specify); 999 = Missing. If R volunteers anorexia, code no.

ElementDescription: Specify the medical disorder
Were you ever greatly concerned about eating too much, looking too fat, or gaining too much weight?
Have you ever been treated for an eating disorder?
When was that?
Has there ever been a time in your life when you went on eating binges -- eating a large amount of food in a short period of time (usually less than 2 hours)?
Notes: 1 = No (Skip to PT1); 3 = Alc/Drug Only; 5 = Yes, clean; 6 = Both A/D and clean; 999 = Missing
